(ABSTRACT) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This memo establishes naming conventions, metadata requirements, and) show newline
(scope rules for documentation in the Library of Cyberspace. We adopt) show newline
(Internet Engineering Task Force \(IETF\) RFC format for technical) show newline
(compatibility while using "memo" as our vernacular. The IETF and its) show newline
(associated organizations serve as the normative model for our standards) show newline
(processes, though unlike the IETF, membership is restricted to United) show newline
(States citizens.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(STATUS OF THIS MEMO) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This document is an Informational memo for the Library of Cyberspace) show newline
(community. It establishes conventions for penning memos and normative) show newline
(references to external standards bodies.) show newline
() show newline
(Distribution of this memo is unlimited.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(MOTIVATION) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The IETF's "Request for Comments" name reflects a historical process we) show newline
(don't share. We don't request comments--we record decisions. But the RFC) show newline
(format is well-understood and serves our needs.) show newline
() show newline
(The compromise: RFC format externally, "memo" internally.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    "I penned a memo on wormholes"     <- what we say) show newline
(    "See Memo-041"                       <- how we cite) show newline
() show newline
(The IETF has successfully governed Internet standards for over 35 years) show newline
(through open processes, rough consensus, and running code. We adopt) show newline
(their model not from lack of imagination but from recognition of what) show newline
(works.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(TERMINOLOGY) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Term      Meaning                                                ) show newline
(  memo      Any document in the Library of Cyberspace              ) show newline
(  RFC       A memo published in RFC format with canonical number   ) show newline
(  pen       To author a memo                                       ) show newline
(  promote   To elevate scope \(local -> federation -> core\)         ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
