(https://www.rfc-editor.org/) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Normative RFCs) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  RFC        Title                                             Relevance                              ) show newline
(  RFC 2026   The Internet Standards Process, Revision 3        Standards track, categories, process   ) show newline
(  RFC 2119   Key Words for Use in RFCs                         MUST, SHOULD, MAY terminology          ) show newline
(  RFC 3935   A Mission Statement for the IETF                  Rough consensus, running code          ) show newline
(  RFC 7322   RFC Style Guide                                   Document formatting                    ) show newline
(  RFC 8174   Ambiguity of Uppercase vs Lowercase in RFC 2119   Keyword clarification                  ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(RFC 2119 Keywords) show newline
(-----------------) show newline
() show newline
(The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "REQUIRED", "SHALL", "SHALL NOT",) show newline
("SHOULD", "SHOULD NOT", "RECOMMENDED", "MAY", and "OPTIONAL" in Library) show newline
(of Cyberspace documents are to be interpreted as described in RFC 2119) show newline
(and RFC 8174.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(ADOPTED PRACTICES) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(What we take from IETF:) show newline
() show newline
(  * RFC format - Document structure, numbering, required sections) show newline
(  * RFC 2119 keywords - MUST, SHOULD, MAY precision) show newline
(  * Security Considerations - Required in every specification) show newline
(  * Rough consensus - General agreement over voting) show newline
(  * Running code - Implementations validate specifications) show newline
() show newline
(These practices provide precision without bureaucracy, ensuring) show newline
(specifications are unambiguous while remaining accessible to) show newline
(implementers.) show newline
() show newline
(What we skip:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Working group charters) show newline
(  * Area director approval) show newline
(  * IESG review cycles) show newline
(  * Last call periods) show newline
(  * IANA registry formalism) show newline
() show newline
(Simple. Direct. We document, we build, we ship.) show newline
() show newline
